<bug>
    <id>40030</id>
    <title>mod_dav documentation could be improved (to &lt;LimitExcept ...&gt;)</title>
    <description>
        <paragraph id="1">
            <sentence id="1.1">The documentaiton page at http://httpd.apache.org/docs/2.2/mod/mod_dav.html</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="2">
            <sentence id="2.1">Has:</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="3">
            <sentence id="3.1">&lt;LimitExcept GET OPTIONS&gt;
  require user admin
&lt;/LimitExcept&gt;</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="4">
            <sentence id="4.1">This example does not seem the best general purpose case since it omits the HEAD
and POST options, which would allow to standard URL access to occur but
correctly limit methods employed by DAV.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="5">
            <sentence id="5.1">&lt;LimitExcept GET HEAD OPTIONS POST&gt;
  require user admin
&lt;/LimitExcept&gt;</sentence>
        </paragraph>
    </description>
</bug>
